-- Harlequins, Toulouse, Toulon Stay Perfect in Heineken Cup Rugby
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-12-08T20:18:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-08/harlequins-toulouse-toulon-stay-perfect-in-heineken-cup-rugby.html
Harlequins, Toulouse and Toulon all
won to maintain their perfect records after three matches in
rugby union’s Heineken Cup.  Harlequins routed Zebre 57-14 and leads Pool 3 in  Europe ’s
elite club competition with 14 points, six more than Connacht,
which beat Biarritz 22-14 last night.  Toulouse defeated second-place Ospreys 30-14 to open an
eight-point lead in Pool 2. Toulon has a nine-point lead over
Sale in Pool 6 after beating the Sharks 17-6.  Munster defeated Saracens 15-9 to leave both teams tied at
the top of Pool 1 with 10 points, two more than Racing Metro,
which beat Edinburgh 19-9. The Exeter Chiefs beat the Scarlets
22-16 for their first win in Pool 5.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  